The paper discusses the use of Deep Learning (DL) models for various tasks such as image classification, object detection, and machine translation, which are typically covered under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on benchmarking DL models on CPUs, which falls under the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, and cs.NE.
